[
  {
    "id": "rev-0000000001",
    "business_id": "biz-cafe-eclectic-01",
    "rating": "5",
    "text": "This is my Saturday morning anchor. Sandra and I come here every week after my radio broadcast and the avocado toast never disappoints. Staff knows us by name at this point.",
    "user_name": "Ava R.",
    "time_created": "2026-01-11T10:22:00"
  },
  {
    "id": "rev-0000000002",
    "business_id": "biz-cafe-eclectic-01",
    "rating": "5",
    "text": "Quiet enough for conversation, good enough to linger. The sweet tea here is perfect - no alcohol needed when the atmosphere is this warm.",
    "user_name": "Liam T.",
    "time_created": "2025-12-28T10:45:00"
  },
  {
    "id": "rev-0000000003",
    "business_id": "biz-cafe-eclectic-01",
    "rating": "4",
    "text": "Reliable brunch spot in Cooper-Young. Gets busy around 10 but worth the short wait.",
    "user_name": "Noah K.",
    "time_created": "2025-12-10T11:10:00"
  },
  {
    "id": "rev-0000000004",
    "business_id": "biz-smokestack-bbq-02",
    "rating": "5",
    "text": "The pulled pork here is the real deal. Tender, smoky, just enough sauce. I brought Pastor Greer after Sunday service and he declared it divine providence.",
    "user_name": "Mia S.",
    "time_created": "2025-12-01T14:15:00"
  },
  {
    "id": "rev-0000000005",
    "business_id": "biz-smokestack-bbq-02",
    "rating": "5",
    "text": "Best BBQ in Midtown. The sides are just as good as the meat - don't skip the baked beans.",
    "user_name": "Ethan B.",
    "time_created": "2025-11-22T13:30:00"
  },
  {
    "id": "rev-0000000006",
    "business_id": "biz-country-table-03",
    "rating": "5",
    "text": "Sunday brunch here is a tradition for us. The fried chicken and cornbread take me back to my grandmother's table. Warm, unhurried service.",
    "user_name": "Zoe M.",
    "time_created": "2025-12-24T12:45:00"
  },
  {
    "id": "rev-0000000007",
    "business_id": "biz-country-table-03",
    "rating": "4",
    "text": "Honest, soul-satisfying comfort food. Mac and cheese is the standout. A little loud on weekends but the food makes up for it.",
    "user_name": "Lucas P.",
    "time_created": "2025-10-26T13:00:00"
  },
  {
    "id": "rev-0000000008",
    "business_id": "biz-midtown-pages-05",
    "rating": "5",
    "text": "A bookshop that feels like it was built just for you. Found the new Barbara Kingsolver and a Howard Thurman collection I'd been looking for. The staff recommendations are genuinely thoughtful.",
    "user_name": "Emma W.",
    "time_created": "2026-01-05T15:30:00"
  },
  {
    "id": "rev-0000000009",
    "business_id": "biz-midtown-pages-05",
    "rating": "5",
    "text": "Independent bookshops like this are why Cooper-Young is special. Great theology and memoir sections.",
    "user_name": "Mason D.",
    "time_created": "2025-12-05T16:20:00"
  },
  {
    "id": "rev-0000000010",
    "business_id": "biz-mitchells-flowers-06",
    "rating": "5",
    "text": "I send flowers to my mother through Mitchell's every few weeks. Arrangements are always fresh and they know Memphis tastes. Zinnias and black-eyed Susans done beautifully.",
    "user_name": "Olivia F.",
    "time_created": "2026-01-07T09:05:00"
  },
  {
    "id": "rev-0000000011",
    "business_id": "biz-mitchells-flowers-06",
    "rating": "4",
    "text": "Reliable local florist. Called same-day and they put together something lovely for a hospital visit. Good people.",
    "user_name": "Jack H.",
    "time_created": "2025-11-14T10:30:00"
  },
  {
    "id": "rev-0000000012",
    "business_id": "biz-bluff-city-auto-07",
    "rating": "4",
    "text": "Brought my 2021 Camry in for an oil change and tire rotation. No pressure, honest quote, done on time. Hard to find that combination. Will come back.",
    "user_name": "Sofia L.",
    "time_created": "2025-10-30T11:00:00"
  },
  {
    "id": "rev-0000000013",
    "business_id": "biz-grace-community-08",
    "rating": "5",
    "text": "Home. Pastor Greer has shepherded this congregation for decades with grace and wisdom. The music, the community, the Sunday dinner after service - this is what church is supposed to feel like.",
    "user_name": "Leo G.",
    "time_created": "2025-10-13T13:45:00"
  },
  {
    "id": "rev-0000000014",
    "business_id": "biz-shelby-farms-park-13",
    "rating": "5",
    "text": "My Greenline walks here 3-4 times a week keep me grounded. The trail is well-maintained, never feels overcrowded in the early mornings. Birdsong is a bonus.",
    "user_name": "Nora V.",
    "time_created": "2025-12-19T07:15:00"
  },
  {
    "id": "rev-0000000015",
    "business_id": "biz-bluff-city-coffee-16",
    "rating": "4",
    "text": "Good stop on the way to the WGSP studio on Saturday mornings. The cold brew is strong enough to carry you through a two-hour live broadcast.",
    "user_name": "Owen C.",
    "time_created": "2026-01-01T06:10:00"
  },
  {
    "id": "rev-0000000016",
    "business_id": "biz-soul-fish-cafe-17",
    "rating": "5",
    "text": "The catfish here is everything. Light, crispy, never greasy. Sandra and I come here when Cafe Eclectic is packed. Excellent sweet tea.",
    "user_name": "Ruby A.",
    "time_created": "2025-11-17T12:30:00"
  },
  {
    "id": "rev-0000000017",
    "business_id": "biz-soul-fish-cafe-17",
    "rating": "4",
    "text": "Neighborhood gem. Grilled salmon option is a solid lighter choice. Friendly and fast.",
    "user_name": "Eli N.",
    "time_created": "2025-11-29T13:00:00"
  },
  {
    "id": "rev-0000000018",
    "business_id": "biz-elmwood-cemetery-12",
    "rating": "5",
    "text": "I come here often to remember. More than a cemetery - it's Memphis history in stone. Walking the grounds is quietly powerful. I always leave feeling connected to something larger.",
    "user_name": "Iris J.",
    "time_created": "2026-01-03T09:30:00"
  },
  {
    "id": "rev-0000000019",
    "business_id": "biz-wgsp-1490-studio-14",
    "rating": "5",
    "text": "WGSP feels like community radio the way it's supposed to feel. Morning Reflections with Rebecca is the highlight of my Saturday. Real voices, real Memphis.",
    "user_name": "Cole M.",
    "time_created": "2025-12-14T08:45:00"
  },
  {
    "id": "rev-0000000020",
    "business_id": "biz-kroger-midtown-04",
    "rating": "4",
    "text": "My weekly staple. Produce section is reliable, the store brand items are solid, and the pharmacy fills prescriptions without drama. Gets crowded Friday evenings but manageable.",
    "user_name": "Maya D.",
    "time_created": "2026-01-11T17:00:00"
  },
